			<description><![CDATA[<p>
You are multi-skilled, passionate, and a consultative problem solver dedicated to making our customers amazingly successful. We are looking for a driven individual who enjoys working directly with customers to understand requirements, help customers get setup and trained on vidIQ for long term success, and providing best practice advice and training on our platform.</p>
<p>
As a key member of our Client Strategist team, you will be an expert and advocate who will lead, develop and execute on implementation plans that will make our customers extremely successful with vidIQ. The ideal candidate for this role will be customer oriented with strong communication and analytical skills. In addition, we are seeking someone who is technically oriented, has project management expertise, passion for social media, reporting and functional analytic knowledge. You must be able to articulate value, inspire and be comfortable consulting our customers.</p>
<p>
<strong>Role &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
Project lead and implement vidIQ project roll outs including: project management, project tracking, requirements analysis, customer feedback sessions, dashboard customization and configurations, and analytic report creation<br />
Possess an in-depth understanding of vidIQ&rsquo;s suite of products and services<br />
Grow the services team by developing assets, resources, knowledge base, and training content to develop scalable processes<br />
Independently drive and lead an emerging department<br />
Prepares easy to understand presentation elements<br />
Arranges and drafts agendas, prepares related background material, takes minutes and follows up on action items from meetings in a timely manner<br />
Deliver with the mindset of &ldquo;Customer Success&rdquo; at all times, driving industry best practices<br />
Required Skills &amp; Experience</p>
<br />
<p>
<strong>Bachelors degree or relevant work experience</strong>At least 3+ years experience in a B2B customer centric environment<br />
Relevant work experience in account management, business analysis, consulting, or other implementation &amp; delivery type roles<br />
An in-depth knowledge and passion for the social media space and analytics<br />
